 ssh -i /home/durgesh_devops/devop_ec2.pem


Step 1:ssh ubuntu@Public IPv4 address, and enter.
Step 2: Say 'yes' for fingerprint
Step 3: Provide key value pair with the command ( ssh -i file location)
# Example: ssh -i /home/durgesh_devops/devop_ec2.pem ubuntu@Public IPv4 address

Step 4: Keep the permision closed with the cammond (chmod 600 /home/durgesh_devops/devop_ec2.pem)

Step 5: Now directly run the command (  ssh -i /home/durgesh_devops/devop_ec2.pem ubuntu@Public IPv4 address)

